title: [? if class_war : Class War ?][? if reconcile_business : Capital Flight ?]
new-page: true
is-card: true
on-arrival: class_war_timer += 6; month_actions += 1; nationalize_budget = 4; nationalize_budget -= 1 if works_councils >= 2; nationalize_budget -= 1 if works_councils >= 3; nationalize_budget -= 1 if socializations + nationalization_progress >= 2;
view-if: capital_strike_seen and class_war_timer <= 0
card-image: img/class_war.jpg
tags: govt_affairs

= [? if class_war : Class War ?][? if reconcile_business : Capital Flight ?]

Due to our policies, an economic crisis has triggered. Some in our party consider this a result of our policies, others blame the bourgeoisie. Regardless, something has to be done.

[? if not approach_adopted : We are yet to adopt an approach. Until we do, we are limited in the scope of our response. ?]

[? if class_war >= 5 : We have adopted the revolutionary approach, certifying the crisis as a manufacturing of the bourgeoisie against us, which we must combat by completing the revolution. ?]

[? if reconcile_business >= 5 : We have adopted the rightist approach, certifying the crisis as a result of our policies, which failed to account for the fact that worker well-being depends upon healthy investment in the economy. ?]

- @revolutionary_approach: The class war intensifies.
- @right_approach: Clearly, a failure in our governance.
- @address: What can we do?
- @easy_discard

@revolutionary_approach
view-if: class_war < 5 and reconcile_business < 5
subtitle: The Marxist strategy of the SPD has always been to provoke a confrontation with the capitalists through socialist reforms, through which the rupture leading into socialist transformation would occur. Now, the time for this rupture has come.
on-arrival: reformist_dissent += 10; left_strength += 10; left_dissent -= 10; class_war += 1; class_war += 1 if left_plan_adopted
go-to: address

The revolutionaries of the party put forward their proposed approach to the crisis. They say that this is a success of our strategies, so long as we take it to the next level and wage the class war from below, just as the businesses now do so from above by seeking to bleed the economy dry.

[? if class_war < 5 : The approach has not yet been adopted. It will take more convincing. ?]

[? if class_war >= 5 : The approach has been adopted! We can now work on waging the class struggle. ?]

@right_approach
view-if: reconcile_business < 5 and class_war < 5
subtitle: Our goal is, ultimately, to improve the living conditions of the workers. We can only do this through constructive governance; not through crises that we directly manufacture through our policies. We have failed, and must remedy this failure.
on-arrival: left_dissent += 10; reformist_strength += 10; reformist_dissent -= 10; reconcile_business += 1; reconcile_business += 1 if wtb_adopted or weimar_plan_adopted
go-to: address

The rightists of the party put forward their proposed approach to the crisis. They say that this is a failure of our strategies, a result of us failing to account for the business community's opinions in our haste to deliver for the workers, and that the transition to socialism must be a gradual process which at all steps benefits the worker, without economic crises.

[? if reconcile_business < 5 : The approach has not yet been adopted. It will take more convincing. ?]

[? if reconcile_business >= 5 : The approach has been adopted! We can now work on winning back business. ?]

@address
subtitle: We must address the crisis as it stands.

We must focus on the immediate crisis. 

- @seize
- @capital_controls
- @propaganda
- @business
- @party_financing
- @socialize_media
- @idling
- @establish_councils
- @dvp_reach
- @nothing

@seize
title: Empower workers to seize the factories!
view-if: capital_occupations != 1
max-visits: 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_strength <= reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength : The bulk of the party does not support this radical action. ?] [? if judicial_reform < 3 : The judiciary would oppose this action. ?] [? if rb_militancy < 0.25 : If we increased the strength of our paramilitary forces, perhaps we could do this. ?] [? if works_councils < 1 : We need the support of the works councils first. ?][? if left_coalition+sapd_r < 50 : The Reichstag is opposed. ?][? if class_war < 1 : This is contrary to our strategy with regards to the crisis. ?]
choose-if: class_war >= 1 and left_strength > reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength and (judicial_reform >= 3 or rb_militancy >= 0.25) and works_councils >= 1 and ((left_coalition+sapd_r >= 50) or (rb_force+rfb_force >= 50))
on-arrival: class_war += 1; bourgeois_power -= 0.07; nationalization_progress += 1; coup_progress += 6; unemployed -= 2; unemployed -= 1 if works_councils >= 3; works_program += 1; workers_spd += 10*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 10*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 2; dvp_relation -= 4; workers_nsdap -= 8*(1-dissent); unemployed_nsdap -= 8*(1-dissent); left_strength += 15; reformist_dissent += 10; left_dissent -= 10; factory_takeovers += 1; economic_growth += 2; socialism += 3; capital_occupations = 1

If the capitalists are going to attack us, then we must hit them back. We have empowered the workers to seize and take full control of the factories that the capitalists have idled. The fascists, of course, call us thieves and looters.


@capital_controls
title: Enact capital controls to lessen the impact.
view-if: capital_controls != 1
max-visits: 1
choose-if: judicial_reform >= 2 and (left_coalition+sapd_r >= 50) or (popular_front+sapd_r >= 50 and z_relation >= 60 or (z_party_leader == "Joos" and z_relation >= 40))
unavailable-subtitle: [? if judicial_reform < 2 : The judiciary would never allow this. ?][? if judicial_reform >= 2 : The Reichstag is opposed. ?]
on-arrival: unemployed -= 1.5; bourgeois_power -= 0.03; workers_spd += 6*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 6*(1-dissent); economic_growth += 2; capital_controls = 1

Capital controls might blunt some of the worst economic components of the capital strike.



@propaganda
title: Launch a propaganda campaign blaming the capitalists for the crisis.
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: (radio >= 2 or commercialized_media >= 3) and resources >= 1
max-visits: 1
view-if: capital_propaganda != 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if radio < 2 and commercialized_media < 3 : We have not built up our media enough. ?] [? if resources < 1: We do not have enough resources. ?]
on-arrival: workers_spd += 7*(1-dissent); new_middle_spd += 6*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 6*(1-dissent); pro_republic += 5*(1-dissent); resources -= 1; socialism += 5; capital_propaganda = 1

We launch a counter-propaganda campaign to blame the economic crisis on the capitalists, using all of our media channels to do so. Because of our existing media framework, this is moderately successful in directing popular criticisms towards the capitalists and away from us.

@business
title: Meet with business leaders to try and win them back over.
view-if: not capital_reconcile
max-visits: 1
choose-if: reformist_strength > left_strength+center_strength and dvp_relation >= 30 and reconcile_business >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if reformist_strength < left_strength+center_strength : The bulk of the party does not support this moderate action. ?][? if dvp_relation < 35 : We have no contacts with the business company. ?][? if reconcile_business < 1 : This is contrary to our strategy with regards to the crisis. ?]
on-arrival: reconcile_business += 1; economic_growth += 0.3; unemployed -= 0.2; inflation -= 0.2; bourgeois_power += 0.02; socialism -= (5*bourgeois_power); coup_progress -= 1; coalition_dissent -= 1; dvp_relation += 3; reformist_strength += 15; left_dissent += 10; reformist_dissent -= 10; bourgeoisie_dnvp *= 0.9; bourgeoisie_nsdap *= 0.9; bourgeoisie_dvp += 5

We meet with several leaders from the business community to try and assuage their concerns. Though little progress is made, we think we have at least established contacts through which we might continue in the future.

@party_financing
title: Ban private financing of political parties.
view-if: class_war >= 4
max-visits: 1
choose-if: (left_coalition+sapd_r >= 50) and (judicial_reform >= 4)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_coalition+sapd_r < 50 : The Reichstag opposes this. ?][? if judicial_reform < 4 : The judiciary would not allow this. ?]
on-arrival: financing_banned = 1; class_war += 1; economic_growth -= 1*bourgeois_power; unemployed += 0.7*bourgeois_power; inflation += 0.5*bourgeois_power; bourgeois_power -= 0.05; coup_progress += 3; socialism += 3; coalition_dissent += 5; dvp_relation -= 20; z_relation -= 10; ddp_relation -= 10

We ban private financing of political parties, the backbone of all the bourgeois parties which rely on industrialist support to fund their reactionary activities. Understandably, they now hate us.

@socialize_media
title: Socialize mass media, wrestling it from private ownership.
view-if: class_war >= 5
max-visits: 1
choose-if: (left_coalition+sapd_r >= 50) and (judicial_reform >= 5)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_coalition+sapd_r < 50 : The Reichstag opposes this. ?][? if judicial_reform < 4 : The judiciary would not allow this. ?]
on-arrival: socialized_media = 1; class_war += 1; economic_growth -= 3*bourgeois_power; unemployed += 2*bourgeois_power; inflation += 1*bourgeois_power; bourgeois_power -= 0.1; coup_progress += 5; socialism += 5; coalition_dissent += 5; dvp_relation -= 20; z_relation -= 15; ddp_relation -= 15; reformist_dissent += 5

We have chosen to socialize mass media, one of the many ways through which capitalism controls mass information and maintains popular support. By dismantling the bourgeoisie's control over the narrative, we attack one of the pillars of their power. How should we go about this socialization?

- @state_run: The news will be state-run, at least for now.
- @union_run: The news will be run by existing democratic workers' organizations.

@state_run
subtitle: -1 budget
on-arrival: state_media = 1; socialism += 5; workers_spd += 4; unemployed_spd += 4; new_middle_spd += 4; old_middle_spd += 4; rural_spd += 3; budget -= 1; inflation += 0.6 if budget < 0; reformist_dissent += 10; pro_republic -= 5; labor_dissent += 5; center_dissent += 10;

We have established a state-run news agency, albeit still in its infancy, to replace private ownership. There is talk of establishing a corresponding ministry to manage this agency, and it is not clear yet if we intend to establish an independent board to run the news agencies or if we intend to maintain them under state control.

## todo: unlock whole-new ministry for press!

@union_run
subtitle: [? if not radio : -1 resource ?]
choose-if: resources >= 1 or radio
unavailable-subtitle: We cannot afford to take over the presses. 
on-arrival: resources -= 1 if not radio; labor_strength += 10; labor_dissent -= 10; workers_spd += (labor_strength/10)

We have handed the presses over to existing democratic workers' organizations, most namely trade unions. We will consider a more permanent solution at another time.

@idling
title: Nationalize the idling factories.
max-visits: 1
view-if: class_war >= 3
subtitle: -[+ nationalize_budget +] budget. [? if works_councils >= 3 : Our works councils have reduced the budget necessary for this program. ?] [? if socializations >= 2: Our existing socialization policies have reduced the budget necessary for this program. ?]
choose-if: economic_minister_party != "DVP" and left_coalition+sapd_r >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: [? if economic_minister_party == "DVP" : The DVP-controlled Economic Ministry could never allow such an action. ?][? if left_coalition+sapd_r < 50 : The Reichstag is opposed. ?]
go-to: nationalize_no_deficit if budget >= nationalize_budget; nationalize_deficit if budget < nationalize_budget

@nationalize_no_deficit
on-arrival: nationalization_progress += 1; class_war += 1; capital_strike_progress += 2; bourgeois_power -= 0.05; unemployed -= 3.5 if unemployed >= 6; unemployed -= 1.2 if works_councils >= 3; workers += 2 if nationalization_progress < 2; budget -= nationalize_budget; works_program += 1; workers_spd += 8*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 5*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 1; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_grand_coalition; dvp_relation -= 4; left_dissent -= 5; new_middle_spd -= 2; new_middle_spd += 1 if new_middle_conscious; old_middle_spd -= 3; economy_goal_completed += 1; inflation += 2; economic_growth += 1.7 if economic_growth < 5
achievement: wirtschaftspolitik

[? if nationalization_progress == 1 : We have begun purchasing idling enterprises from the capitalists[? if works_councils >= 1: , and running them in coordination with empowered works councils ?]. By keeping production going, we can stave off the rising unemployment. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress == 1 : The Left argues that this should only be a first step in the socialist transformation of the economy. Eventually, much of the economy must be brought under popular control. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress > 1 : We purchase additional underutilized enterprises and run them in a coordinated socialist fashion with the works councils, hiring formerly laid off workers. A significant portion of the economy is now under public control. ?]

@nationalize_deficit
on-arrival: socialism -= 2; class_war += 1

Unfortunately, we do not have the budget to begin buying out industrial facilities. Some are urging for deficit spending in order to purchase factories, while others are encouraging (currently illegal) factory takeovers by workers, or nationalization without compensation. Taking any of these actions would require a vast departure from our previous party stances.

- @nationalize_deficit_1
- @nationalize_without_compensation
- @empower_workers
- @return: No, we should not do this.


@nationalize_deficit_1
title: Take a budget deficit to fund the nationalization program.
choose-if: (left_strength > reformist_strength + center_strength or woytinsky_advisor == 1) and (finance_minister_party == "SPD" or finance_minister_party == "KPD")
subtitle: [? if woytinsky_advisor: Woytinsky can bring us around to supporting a budget deficit. ?]
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_strength <= reformist_strength + center_strength: The party does not yet support budget deficits for this purpose. ?] [? if not woytinsky_advisor : Perhaps bringing on an advisor might help make this action palatable? ?][? if finance_minister_party != "SPD" and finance_minister_party != "KPD" : Without control over finances, we cannot undertake such deficit spending. ?]
on-arrival: nationalization_progress += 1; bourgeois_power -= 0.05; capital_strike_progress += 3; unemployed -= 3 if unemployed >= 6; unemployed -= 1.2 if works_councils >= 3; budget -= nationalize_budget; works_program += 1; workers_spd += 8*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 5*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 2; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_grand_coalition; dvp_relation -= 7; z_relation -= 4; new_middle_spd -= 3; new_middle_spd += 1 if new_middle_conscious; old_middle_spd -= 3; economy_goal_completed += 1; inflation += 3; economic_growth += 2 if economic_growth < 5;
achievement: wirtschaftspolitik

[? if woytinsky_advisor: Most of the party, even on the left, are opposed to budget deficits for any purpose, with the exception of Wladimir Woytinsky. While he did not originally support the left's "transformational" plan, he has come around, and has persuaded the party and the Finance Ministry to support budget deficits in limited cases, for the purpose of exiting from the depression. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress == 1 : We have begun purchasing idling enterprises from the capitalists[? if works_councils >= 1: , and running them in coordination with empowered works councils ?]. By keeping production going, we can stave off the rising unemployment. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress == 1 : The Left argues that this should only be a first step in the socialist transformation of the economy. Eventually, much of the economy must be brought under popular control. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress > 1 : We purchase additional underutilized enterprises and run them in a coordinated socialist fashion with the works councils, hiring formerly laid off workers. A significant portion of the economy is now under public control. ?]

@nationalize_without_compensation
title: Nationalize without compensation.
subtitle: There is no reason why we should not simply take over idle factories. This is likely to provoke a confrontation with the capitalists.
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_strength <= reformist_strength + center_strength: The bulk of the party does not support this quasi-legal action. ?] [? if judicial_reform < 3 : The judiciary would oppose this action. ?] [? if left_coalition < 50 : We lack a majority in the Reichstag. ?]
choose-if: left_strength > reformist_strength + center_strength and judicial_reform >= 3 and left_coalition >= 50
on-arrival: nationalization_progress += 1; bourgeois_power -= 0.1; capital_strike_progress += 7; coup_progress += 3; unemployed -= 2.5 if unemployed >= 6; unemployed -= 1.2 if works_councils >= 3 and unemployed >= 3; works_program += 1; workers_spd += 8*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 6*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 2; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_grand_coalition; coalition_dissent += 1 if capital_strike_progress >= 10; dvp_relation -= 12; z_relation -= 8; ddp_relation -= 8; left_strength += 15; reformist_dissent += 10; left_dissent -= 10; new_middle_spd -= 5; new_middle_spd += 3 if new_middle_conscious; old_middle_spd -= 8; economy_goal_completed += 1; kpd_relation += 5*(1-dissent); inflation += 4; economic_growth += 1 if economic_growth < 4; socialism -= 1
achievement: wirtschaftspolitik

The capitalists are, predictably, up in arms about our policy of nationalization without compensation. They call it illegal expropriation, and it is. Nevertheless, it is clear that they have failed by keeping their factories idle, and we must take radical action.

[? if nationalization_progress == 1 : We have begun acquiring idling enterprises from the capitalists[? if works_councils >= 1: , and running them in coordination with empowered works councils ?]. By keeping production going, we can stave off the rising unemployment. ?]

[? if nationalization_progress > 1 : We acquired additional underutilized enterprises and run them in a coordinated socialist fashion with the works councils, hiring formerly laid off workers. A significant portion of the economy is now under public control. ?]

@empower_workers
title: Empower workers to take over factories.
subtitle: We can promise to legalize factory occupations, giving the factories over to worker unions. This is highly confrontational, and would likely provoke a reaction from right-wing militants as well as capitalists.
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_strength <= reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength : The bulk of the party does not support this radical action. ?] [? if judicial_reform < 3 : The judiciary would oppose this action. ?] [? if rb_militancy < 0.25 : If we increased the strength of our paramilitary forces, perhaps we could do this. ?] [? if works_councils < 1 : We need the support of the works councils first. ?][? if left_coalition < 50 : We lack a majority in the Reichstag. ?]
choose-if: left_strength > reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength and (judicial_reform >= 3 or rb_militancy >= 0.25) and works_councils >= 1 and left_coalition >= 50
on-arrival: nationalization_progress += 1; bourgeois_power -= 0.1; capital_strike_progress += 6; coup_progress += 5; unemployed -= 3 if unemployed >= 6; unemployed -= 1.5 if works_councils >= 3 and unemployed > 4; works_program += 1; workers_spd += 10*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 10*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 2; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_grand_coalition; coalition_dissent += 1 if capital_strike_progress >= 10; coalition_dissent += 1 if coup_progress >= 8; dvp_relation -= 12; z_relation -= 8; ddp_relation -= 8; workers_nsdap -= 5*(1-dissent); unemployed_nsdap -= 5*(1-dissent); left_strength += 15; reformist_dissent += 10; left_dissent -= 10; new_middle_spd -= 5; new_middle_spd += 2 if new_middle_conscious; old_middle_spd -= 10; factory_takeovers += 1; economy_goal_completed += 1; kpd_relation += 5*(1-dissent); inflation += 3; economic_growth += 1 if economic_growth < 3; socialism += 1
achievement: wirtschaftspolitik

The capitalists are, predictably, up in arms about our policy of legalizing factory occupations. They call it illegal expropriation, and it is. Nevertheless, it is clear that they have failed, and we must take radical action.

Fascists have been taking increasingly violent actions around the occupied factories, calling us thieves and looters. However, the some of the working-class supporters of the fascists have been peeled off, or at least the ones with a sense of class solidarity.

@establish_councils
title: Establish workers' councils in occupied factories, to coordinate industrial action.
view-if: factory_takeovers >= 1 and class_war >= 5 and not supreme_soviet
max-visits: 1
choose-if: resources >= 2 or (resources >= 1 and works_councils >= 3)
subtitle: [? if works_councils < 3 : -2 resources ?][? if works_councils >= 3 : -1 resource ?]
on-arrival: soviets_exist = 1; resources -= 1; resources -= 1 if works_councils < 3; bourgeois_power -= (0.02*factory_takeovers); rb_militancy += (0.01*factory_takeovers); workers_spd += (factory_takeovers*2); unemployed_spd += factory_takeovers; socialism += factory_takeovers

We have established workers' councils in those factories which we occupy, helping to organize the occupied factories with each other and through existing works councils. These soviets also lay the groundwork for a parallel state apparatus.

@dvp_reach
title: Reach out to the DVP.
view-if: reconcile_business >= 3 and dvp_relation < 50
choose-if: resources >= 1
subtitle: -1 resource. [? if dvp_relation < 35 : We are unlikely to see much success. ?]
on-arrival: dvp_relation += 5; resources -= 1; socialism -= 2; economic_growth += 0.5 if dvp_relation >= 35; unemployed -= 0.3 if dvp_relation >= 35

We reach out to the DVP, attempting to use them as an intermediary through which to restore the trust and confidence of the business community.

@nothing
title: There is nothing we can do.

There is nothing we can do that is within constitutional and legal bounds.

